metadata.name: The Yawning Monkey
metadata.description:
The Real Bored Ape üêí
Traveling through the forest, came across this sleeping monkey. He sat on those rocks and slept and often yawned.

The bonnet macaque, also known as zati, is a species of macaque endemic to southern India.

Location : Thenmala Reserve Forest, Kerala, India 

Edition : 1/1 

Camera : Nikon D3300 | Lens : Nikkor 70-300mm
